Daniel Witzel</name>
<Time>1532390573130< /Time><rate>5</rate>< text>
I came to Dunn & Platts Dental after almost 5 years of no dental care. Their staff was very understanding and accommodating of my situation, quickly got me in for an initial consultation and a cleaning to follow. My biggest fear of going back to the dentist after such a long time was the potential shaming and disappointment I would get from a dentistry team, however, Dr. Platts and their entire office staff have been very welcoming and have never made me feel ashamed for neglecting my oral health. They have been very kind and are only interested in getting my teeth back to a good clean state and back on track!

In the few fillings I have had done, Dr. Platts and the assistants were very attentive to my comfort, they certainly put my fears of pain aside by ensuring I had enough anesthetic and talking me through each step of the process. As a person who has dreaded and feared going to the dentist, I would highly recommend this office for anyone needing high quality, compassionate dental care.<//text>

<Name>Shaul Rosen-Rager</Name><review>Sometimes you just get lucky.  I have had 6 or 7 GP doctors since moving to Hemet in '96, but only one dentist. Dr. Dunn have been taking care of my teeth for over 20 years. He is a second generation in the Dunn dental dynasty, and must have started when he was 12 because he was already very good when he joined his father Heber ( it was Dunn and Dunn back then.) Dr. Dunn stands behind his work and practically gives a "lifetime warranty" on his dental work. He has a great sense of humor, and always explains the procedure and the different options available.  He is patient and kind, always sensitive to my needs and my tolerance for pain (I have none).
I also love visiting twice yearly the kind and talented dental hygienist Arlene, who's very gentle yet thorough, and doesn't berate me for forgetting to floss under the bridge. But I really shouldn't tell you about her... she is so good, it's already hard to get appointments with her.
Then there's Tayla and the office staff, always friendly, diligently checking with the insurance company and making sure that the estimates, deductables and whatnots are always accurate, so you don't get a surprise bill after the fact. What a team!
Thank you, Team Dunn and Platts! You are the best!</review>< response>

< Review>
Greetings - One of the hardest things to do is find an outstanding and competent health care services in a small and friendly community.  Twelve and half year ago we (my wife and I) moved to the San Jacinto Valley.  We have belonged to one of the world's largest health maintenance organizations for are health needs.  However, we were unable to find a dental care professional in the local area and continued to travel back to our prior home some 50 + miles away to seek dental care and services.  Then about three years ago a neighbor recommended the services of Dr. Dunn, a good and caring dentist.  Being senior citizens, we were hard to please when it came to having a health professional that showed care, compassion and current knowledge in treating the older generation of society.  Thankfully we found the Offices of Dunn & Platt's in the local area of the San Jacinto Valley.  Ever since we have found Dr. Dunn and Dr. Platt and their staff of highly competent and caring dental professionals we found a new home for our dental needs.  We will continue to use their services for continuing dental health needs.  We wish to thank Dr. Dunn and his staff for treating us with such care and professional understand as we continue down our path of life.  The Dental Office of Dunn & Platts come with our highest recommendation and hope you too will their dental services to your liking.< /Review>

<Text>This is a lovely local park with plenty to see and do, and as a bonus the city just recently replaced the playground equipment!  There's a bunch of different things to entertain yourself with here, including a small lake/large pond with a fishing pier, plenty of walking trails including one that goes up to the top of Double Peak mountain, and a huge water fountain for kids to play in on hot summer days!  This park is quite popular so sometimes you'll have a bit of trouble with parking, but so far it hasn't been worse than any other park in SD county that we've visited.< /Text>< Pictures>

<user_id>109118280853041895085</user_id><username>Alyssa Fisher<//username><time>1592944170104<//time><Rate>2<//Rate>< Text>
I have been a Banfield wellness plan customer for 8 years, and recently moved to the area. I took my dog in for a semi-emergency for a wound cleaning and evaluation. After we arrived and checked in for our drop off appointment, we waited over 10 minutes before anyone came out to take my dog to the back, watching others who checked in after us get taken back, before the person who checked us in finally just took my dog back. This happened again when I went to pick up my dog - I paid and then waited, and waited, before the person who checked me out went and got my dog. I understand that they are busy, but this seemed to be an indicator that they easily miss things and set the visit off on the wrong foot.
In addition, the doctor who called was not very responsive to the symptoms and description of the issue and seemed to push an agenda in terms of what they thought was wrong. They charged me for a wound cleaning, bandage, and sent us home with antibiotics and said to come back in 10 days. No one called to follow up on us, which is normal practice for Banfield hospitals that we've visited in the past.
All of this added up to an uneasy feeling for me, so I ended up getting a second opinion at another local vet, who diagnosed my dog with a semi-rare infection that requires a lot more care than we ever would've gotten from Banfield.
As a result of this experience, I have cancelled my wellness plan and moved my dog's care to the other vet - and I won't recommend the Banfield plans to anyone anymore. The level of care that my dog has received at the other  vet in just the past two weeks has FAR exceeded any care I received from any Banfield hospital in the past 8 years.</Text>

<Review>Great atmosphere, amazingly friendly and welcoming staff, fair coffee.
There just seems to be a lack of knowledge surrounding the traditional espresso coffee wares(which I realize is slightly a matter of opinion). I was given a dry cappuccino when asking for a macchiato and had to clarify a few times what was even meant by macchiato.
The black coffee was not as light a roast as I would like but that is purely a matter of taste so no fault there. It wasn't bitter or under extracted so I can't fault the personal decision to select this coffee, nor would I want to. The massive diversity in roasting is what makes discovering new shops so exciting.
The blueberry muffin was very good. Not overly sweet, medium density, subtle blueberry flavor which actually paired quite well with the black coffee.
Was able to try the nitro coffee on my way out which was very good for those who like the texture this process brings but want a more nuanced coffee experience.
Overall I'll be returning to this shop mainly because a.they are in a dry area for decent shops and b. The staff is worth the return trip making any other shortcomings easy to overlook.< /Review>< Rate>
4</Rate>

<Text>I can see why this coffee shop gets raving reviews. Service is wonderful, and the selection is unique and wide. I went for a cappuccino, my usual menu item at any new to me coffee shop. They use different "milk" types, including almond.

If you order your drink to stay, you get it in a beautiful cup that many people posted pictures of. It is so vibrant and colorful! The drink was very good, and the atmosphere quiet and relaxed. On a Saturday afternoon there were few people there, but I can see how during business hours the coffee shop can get quickly filled up. Seating is plentiful, and decor is somewhat rustic with elements of industrial feel. I generally prefer cozier atmosphere, but to each their own.

I will absolutely come back to try their specialties, now that I established that their cappuccino is worth drinking :)<//Text>< Gmap_id>

The Liquid Leaf is one of my favorite coffee shops! I have frequented this spot any time I am in the area since it first opened, and it has only gotten better and better!

<user>116908105953957031906</user>< text>
I don't get to come here as often as I'd like because of where I live, but it is such a treat when I do. Today I tired the blended banana Chai with an add shot. Made with homemade spiced chai! It is sooo good! The drinks and food are just as wonderful as the staff. Jane, the founder, owner, manager, designer, has done such an amazing job of creating an inviting and beautiful environment. In fact, I found out that she fabricated much of the decor herself. I highly recommend visiting this clean and spacious coffee shop and trying the taste of truly hand crafted tea, coffee and smoothies! Next, I'd like to explore the breakfast sandwiches and wraps... Yuummmmm!</text>

< Text>
This place really deserves an 8 star rating. Service was out of this world. The food was amazing. We ordered a thin crust pizza, the crust was thinner than a saltine cracker but oh my gosh. It packed so much flavor without it being all bread. The thin crust was not overly crunchy, just simply perfect. The alcoholic cocktails are made with 3 OZ. of alcohol instead of the average 1 OZ!!! Spectacular prices, extremely clean, cozy, and a great lunch menu. It is divided into 2 sections. Half as a restaurant with quiet dining and the other half sells alcohol; multi-functioning as a liquor store and provides the take-out orders. I believe they sell all the bottles they serve in house. EVERYTHING IN THIS RESTAURANT IS HOMEMADE. We came here with no expectations but they really blew any possible judgements away. Will continue to recommend and come back. Perfect view and location right on Ventura blvd in Sherman oaks, close to studio City.<//Text>

< Text>
Very warm and familial service with real Italian chefs. The lady behind the counter on Friday and Saturday is a wonderful historian and mixologist, changing out the specialty cocktails every week-I mean they have chartreuse!

Negroni and Aperol spritz were very well balanced with her homemade, organic bitters.

I had the pappardelle pasta which was very good and the magherita pizza was hearty. I might recommend less cheese and more basil. Tiramisu was exceptional, so well balanced with the coffee fallacies and fluffy vanilla exterior<//Text>

<user_id>114049324959506411182< /user_id><Name>Gloria 78<//Name><date>1618815054314</date>< Rating>
5</Rating>
< review>
My son had lost his wallet in Simi Valley, and didn‚Äôt realize it until he arrived home in Lancaster. He called the manager of the apartment complex where he thought  he may have dropped it, but no one had turned it in. He figured it was gone for good, when minutes later he received a call from a gentleman who said that he had found it, with everything intact, which included credit cards and a large sum of money. It turned out that this wonderful man is the owner of Big Z! He adamantly refused any sort of reward, so my son ordered two large vegetarian pizzas, hummus, and some baklava to bring home. All I can say is that this was some of the best Mediterranean food I‚Äôve  had in a long time. Everything was fresh, with plenty of toppings on the pizza, and the hummus and baklava were subtly  unique in  a very delightful way. Not only does the owner have incredible integrity, he also runs an establishment that puts out some of the best food of its kind. Thank you, Omar, for setting a wonderful example.< /review>

< Review>
Service was nice and pick up was easy. We ordered combos, rice, veggies, orange chicken  shrimp, and another one with teriyaki chicken.
The rice and vegetables had no flavor, and the shrimp and orange chicken I got tasted like it was microwaved and then they just poured orange sauce over it (instead of it actually being cooked/tossed in the sauce!). Honestly, this reminded me of school lunch teriyaki and orange chicken. The boneless wings also only got some random sauce dumped on it. I immediately did not like the taste or smell of it. We almost spent $30 on that but had a coupon to cut it down to $15. We wanted to try a new place and now we will definitely be sticking to Panda Express, 100x better.< /Review>

<rating>4< /rating>< Text>
We went to grab a quick dinner at Yoshinoya. This was my second time visiting this fast food chain. Unlike other fast foods, Yoshinoya is very healthy and they have hearty meals available. We ordered Large Orange Chicken Bowl, Large Walnut Shrimp Bowl and 6pcs Asian BBQ Wings. I had orange chicken at Panda Express before and I much more prefer their flavor. However, Walnut Shrimp Bowl was very yummy. We ate in one gulp :) Total was around $20 Not bad for that much amount of food. I don't usually like veggies at Fast Food restaurant but Yoshinoya's veggies were crisp and fresh! I recommend getting Walnut Shrimp Bowl for sure!!</Text>

<Resp>None< /Resp>< review>
Excellent food and service.  The restaurant is decorated very well.  There is an outdoor patio for outdoor seating as well as indoor seating.  There is also a private room for larger events.  They start off with a bread basket.  There is balsamic vinegar and olive oil on the table to self-serve.  The balsamic vinegar is very tasty.  Their calamari was woofed down by everyone in 2 seconds flat. The lasagna is really done well.. not too acidic.  The fettuccine with Bolognese was excellent.  The portion of the tortellini with ham and tomato cream sauce was too small.  The pizza was yummy.  However,  I have had better elsewhere. Our water was constantly filled.   Our used dishes were  seldom left long at the table.  The servers exchanged our dirty dishes for new dishes numerous times.  We would definitely come back again for the delicious food and service.</review>

<time>1565837469363</time><Rating>5</Rating>< review>
Delicious! Recommend the gnocchi gorgonzola ... I had no idea gnocchi could be so soft! You can taste the potato in them too, and the gorgonzola sauce is just amazing. The garlic bread is delicious too, and they have a very nice ginger beer for non-alcoholic lovers. Will need to come back to try something new!!

Tried the tortellini ala crema - delicious!! It's not often I find somewhere that does meat-filled pasta, and this does not disappoint. The sauce is wonderfully flavorful too! Also recommend the prosciutto and melon - very tasty and refreshing! Excellent as an appetizer, would definitely get again.</review>

< review>
This is a review for two experiences. One visit was dining in and the security and was for take-out.

Dining in we went to the restaurant in a group of 5. Our server was excellent and answered many menu related questions from our group. The food was delicious, fresh, and just the right serving size. We shared two different salads and each ordered a pasta entree. Everyone was pleased with the food. They also had a good tap list to choose from with some unique offerings.

The take-out experience was during the county's shelter in place. The pizza we had was perfect to share for 2-3 people. I tried the veggie pizza and look forward to trying some of their other toppings soon.< /review>

1521845750851</date>
< Rating>
5</Rating>
< review>
You can always expect to get an amazing meal at Terra Mia. The food selection is very nice and the service is usually very good. On one or two occasions, the food took extremely long to arrive, but it is a rare case for that to happen. I don't drink wine, but I see lots of people bringing their favorite bottle with them. I'm not sure if that means their wine selection is not so good or highly marked up, but it is nice that they offer the flexibility.< /review>

< user>

<Name>The Chop</Name><time>1559592878434< /time><rating>1< /rating>< text>
Sadly, this place has decent reviews, but my wife and I had a horrible experience with the food. Started off with being told to sit anywhere we wanted on the patio, so we did. Two tables who were sat after us we greeted and given menus and a waiter, but 10 minutes later...we still hadn't been acknowledged so I went and told the host. 5 min after that, we were greeted. I asked the waiters recommendation on a bottle of Rose...he recommended the most expensive, but had no tasting notes to go with his rec. I asked if they had Linguini and clams. The waiter told me "no....this is not italian authentic, so we don't have that".  What a lie.  My wife ordered the fetcuini al salmon and I ordered a pesto pasta with salmon on top. We also ordered a calamari fritti to start.  Calamari came out and was soft and chewy.....no crisp at all. I sent it back telling them why. They brought it back 5 min later and they had dumped the calamari back in the oil and killed it. Now it was crispy, chewy grossness. We set it aside, not eating it. Then the pastas came....  Both were horrible. My wife pasta was under al dente, and mine was overcooked....but they were the same noodle. The Salmon was diced into small pieces and incorporated into the dish rather than a nice fillet on top. Salmon was horrible....overcooked beyond done! It tasted and smelled horrible.
After telling the waiter, the manager came over and i very very kindly explained how bad our meal was, pointing out exactly why wit the salmon and the calamari. Then our bill came. They removed my entree, but still charged me for my wife's horrible entree and the sad calamari. The only thing worth paying for was the wine. So in the end, I paid out $90.00 ($40.00 for the wine & $15.00 tip) and left hungry and annoyed. Stopped at in-n-out on the way home, which was 100 times better that Terra Mia. If you like real Italian food, stay far away from this place...NEVER AGAIN!!</text>

<Rating>1< /Rating>< review>
Making a reservation apparently does not mean anything to this restaurant, Other customers with no reservation who got there after my date and I, got seated before us. Maybe its because Im in my early 20's and Im not a priority in their eyes... who knows. Once I was seated I felt unwelcome by the waiter, every time we spoke he gave me a sarcastic sympathetic tone of voice. Worst part was when I wanted to order a beverage with alcohol , the waiter gave me such an sarcastic apologetic tone thinking that i was not of age and Instead he suggested I get a soda... Like seriously ? Once my date and I got our drinks and dinner, it was just disappointing and lacking flavor. when it was time to pay the waiter gave me a look as if I could not afford to be there. It was just such a unpleasant experience, and felt extremely unwelcome. This is the only place I have ever written a review for. I think I'll stay with my usually spot in SF where they actually treat you right, and not talk down to you.< /review>

<userid>100652061023548941072< /userid><Name>Kenji Sasaki< /Name><date>1488395761052</date><rate>5<//rate><review>We held our wedding reception at Terra Mia and are really glad we did! From early on, the co-owners were extremely helpful and accommodating, particularly Daniele. On the day of, we were swamped with wedding related activities, and the owners and wait staff made sure things ran smoothly with table arrangements, decorations, etc while we were absent. During service, wait staff were fantastically smooth and efficient, never in the way, but always available if we needed anything. The manager was able to quickly put together an alternative meal when it turned out one guest couldn't eat something (gorgonzola in the gnocchi). And the food was top-to-bottom great. We had the banquet options of caprese, garlic bread, osobucco, gnocchi, finished with tiramisu. All were delicious and and we heard only compliments from the guests (3/4 of whom were asian and wouldn't mind telling us if anything was wrong!). Wine and cocktail selection was excellent as well. All-in-all, Terra Mia, its owners, and its staff made our wedding reception as high quality as we could have asked, our guests happy, and us able to enjoy the evening with minimal stress. My only regret from the evening is that my brain was so fried with everything else that I think I forgot to tip as much as I wanted. I'll make it up though, next time I'm in the area as I'm sure we'll be coming back!</review>< Pics>

< Text>
We visited the Los Gatos Library for story time. They have story time for preschool aged kids every Tuesday at 1030am. At first I wasn't sure the time was correct as the library doesn't actually open until 11am but upon arrival I saw a sign on the front door that said to enter along the right side of the building, through the garden for story time. Story time lasts from 1030-11am and includes the reading of several books PLUS singing and dancing! Which must be why they do it before the library actually opens. Be sure to come check it out.<//Text>

<rate>3< /rate>< Review>
This place has potential to be 5 star ;however, a few things really held it back. 1. The food you can order to your room is cray expensive and sub par. I was very disappointed in the cream for coffee selection. I would legit be willing to pay for organic half and half. Those little packaged-for-three million-years nasty plastic things are very 2 star motel for a place that brands itself as boutique. Also HOLY COW this room is so small. Not a place you want to do anything but sleep. The view out the window made me feel like the poor people on titanic. The "pool" is like 4"deep hahaha. Which is both great and terrible for kids. Lastly, the only fridge is a tiny wine fridge,lame. The customer service was great, everyone was friendly and accommodating.  There were some nice touches like the caramels, the coffee machine (worthless without decent cream imo) and the beauty of the lobby, but overall I would not book this room again.<//Review>

< text>
2 night stay. First it is a rather new hotel that is understaffed. The hotel attracts a younger crowd attracted to the rooftop especially with the pandemic. Complimentary Nespresso coffee anD small Fiji bottled water. Our experience is rather bad due to a lack of service due to an employee dropping a bag and breaking some $500 sunglasses. They wanted to give us a $50 credit or their insurance company would review it. Based on past reviews, their claim of an insurance company, is like complaining to a North Korean hotel of them damaging something. You walk away and never go back. Also some issues with lack of COVID-19 protocols and cleanliness in the hallways and cleaning of the elevator lobbies. We have not seen this at any other hotels since the pandemic. Sad and could lead to guests getting sick. Again, perhaps stemming from being understaffed. Our room was thoroughly cleaned and therefore the deserve the one star. Lack of service is perhaps indicative of the direction California is going or it could just be lack management and training.<//text>

<user_name>Sydney Alexander< /user_name><userid>109687730577692203288< /userid><GmapID>0x808506678dbb4e9d:0x42e0b868a3373556</GmapID>< rate>

<Response>{'time': 1616533879984, 'text': 'Thank you for your thoughtful feedback and review, Sydney! We do apologize for inconveniences you encountered during your stay, and hope that you were able to connect with our Assistant General Manager about how we can offer you another opportunity to experience Archer as intended.'}</Response>< text>
I loved the hotel and staff. The friendliness and helpfulness of the staff was great. The room was very nice and I enjoyed my stay but it was very pricey for a just ok experience.
When you typically check into a hotel you receive key infomearion about the hotel and amenities as well as local activities or things to do. You also typically get a menu of hotel pricing for add on services.. mini bar, in room ordering etc. I checked in and received my hotel room key and and didn't get any of this information. I know with covid everything should be contactless or paperless, so I just expected an email or digital form. It seemed there were a few qr codes in the room on a tiny handout but it was shrunk down too small to scan.. or possible Pixelated or distorted. Nothing in the mini bar had a price on it and I wanted to open some of the wine, but didn't know how much it was. I also figured I could order in room dining but didn't get a menu. I didn't know what was open or not in the hotel, as nobody advised me.
So I would suggest an update of current accommodations via email or printed out in rooms.
I also noticed there was no clock radio in the room. Although it's not necessary for all hotels, it's expected in higher end ones such as your hotel. I imaged sitting in my room with the sun coming in and relaxing to some tunes on the radio. There was no radio or option for music at all in the room. I honestly expected even a cheap clock radio of some sort. Cheaper hotels now offer blue tooth clock radios. So I just expected something.
I pre-ordered a charcuterie and cheese board and sparkling wine to be in room upon arrival.. that was on time. But the cheese was underwhelming. I thought maybe it would be a selection of cheeses, but the hotel chose and there was blue cheese chosen. Thats such a strong cheese I expect to be asked if I am OK with the choices. I couldn't eat the blue cheese as it was too strong and honestly a waste of money. I just wanted a bit more of a customized experience
The rooftop bar was awesome and had amazing views but there menu was lacking. I am a vegetarian and the only option was the impossible burger.. which you were out of. So I asked if I could have pasta without the shrimp and it was just unslated butter with noodles. It was pretty bad and I got charged full price even with out the shrimp.
Overall stay was nice, but for the price I paid I really expected a bit more</text>

< text>
Felt welcomed on check in with a glass of Chandon which made everything better. The hotel foyer and lounge areas are very well done and look fantastic. We stayed in the deluxe King, the bed was luxurious and the towels felt so soft! The rainfall shower was a nice bonus. The room came with everything you need and lots of USB ports for charging. Our room had an empty wine fridge which is great to store your Napa wine.
Light sleepers will notice that the do not disturb button in your room is incredibly bright at night, but a couple sticky notes seemed to dim the light.
Our room was on the conference level which had a water bottle refilling station. Such a great idea!
Only downside is in the lounge area they were super busy at night so the service was hit and miss. But we were very well looked after by Kirby who was just amazing and totally made our night.<//text>

< Review>
Amazing hotel in the middle of downtown Napa with great service, beautiful rooms, but at a price. The rooftop bar and restaurant are pretty cool with great views of the city. On the weekend the bar is lively and popular with locals. We came up here for Sunday brunch and it is awesome. You get bottomless mimosas and bloody marys. You also get a fruit plate and a plate off cheeses and charcuteries.</Review>

<Text>The Archer is a nice hotel, but it should be exceptional. The arrival experience was smooth, but it should be extraordinary for the price, e.g. a welcome glass of wine.

On the plus side, it's a very nice hotel in terms of decor, the roof deck is beautiful. The rooms and the lobby are upscale and modern.

On the down side, our room was dirty, there was stuff on the floor. The bed was comfortable but the pillows were too flat. It was also very dark, but we had booked a lower tier room because we were only staying one night. The food on the roof deck was pitiful for Napa. It could be amazing, but it's very pedestrian.

<Review>We spent 2 days at this hotel - located in downtown Napa - earlier this month.

Short version: The hotel itself, the service, and the vibe were great. We would stay again and would recommend it to others!

Long version: The hotel is new and has a well-decorated, spacious, open concept lobby area.

Our room was good and functional, although rather "cozy" (smallish in size). The shower was good - spacious and new. We had a Nespresso coffee set inside the room, which was a definite bonus.

Breakfast was served on their beautiful rooftop, though it can get seriously chilly in the morning (at 7am at least)! Staff brought gas heaters and some people brought blankets.

My husband attended some meetings while here and said their conference rooms were very well-equipped.

Note: The hotel is connected with Charlie Palmer Steak, which we dined at and enjoyed!

Would definitely return and highly recommend for a good stay to others.<//Review>< Pictures>
None< /Pictures>

< review>
Cookie, my friend, made reservations for brunch 5 days previous to 11/25 and when we arrived, they could not find them. Things went downhill from there. Service is poor, the brunch buffet food was cold, it took 10 minutes to get a latte, then arrived with no spoon or sugar.  It took another 10 minutes for the waitress to bring these.  Tiles on the outdoor (6th floor) patio are 'temporary' we were told, and my heel promptly got wedged between one of them.  The manager had to take a knife to move the tile to get my heel out.  A huge puddle of water was on the floor directly by my chair and I was told it was from the overnight condensation and it would be mopped up.  No one ever came so I had to put my napkin on the floor to sop up the water,  and no one ever took the menu's off the table. For all the 'millions' spent on this property, part of that should have been spent on training the wait staff to properly take care of clients, and the property should be finished before being open to the public. Needless to say, I will not be back.< /review>

< rate>
4<//rate>
<text>Phenomenal views of Downtown Napa and surrounding hills from rooftop pool, bar, patio, and gym but avoid their live music.

The lobby is equally impressive with a giant, beautifully rendered, topo map of all the wine districts, surveyable from a comfortable assortment of giant arched couches and chairs and circular bar.

Get a room with a view if you want natural light. The ones facing center can feel dark.

This place would get five stars except for their need to supplement the already perfect rooftop experience with really bad live music (think failing to hit high notes of Tears for Fears hits) that permeates the entire floor.

A setting like that needs nothing else and the bad music makes you leave one of the prime reasons for coming here despite all its other beauty.

If they must have live music, hire the phenomenal flamenco guitar player from Alexis Bakery down the street.< /text><pics>None</pics><Resp>{'time': 1571934475300, 'text': "Hi, Jody! < Review>
I seriously dream about coming back to this hotel! It is one of the best I've ever been to. Gorgeous ambiance.. the room was beyond amazing, including a gigantic soaking tub, separate shower,  and plenty of vanity space. The outside patio includes a gas fireplace and views of hot air balloons in the morning. Our room had an espresso machine that we enjoyed as well.  The nightly local treats delivered at turndown was a really fun touch, too. The restaurant inside the hotel is an absolute MUST! It's pricy, but probably one of the most incredible meals you'll ever have. We brought our own wine and didn't get charged a corkage fee. The rooftop bar has some delicious specialty cocktails which we enjoyed too... again, kinda pricy but worth it for the quality and atmosphere.</Review>

<date>1564845700374<//date><Text>Note - We stayed at this property due to an event taking place on the rooftop.

The rooftop view & bar, work out room, pool and location are definitely the highlights of this property.  The rooms are nice but so are several other hotels in the area, especially for the price.  We decided to dine at Charlie Palmer as we have eaten at two different Charlie Palmer restaurants and knew the quality of food.  A SWING AND A MISS at Archer.  It appear the main chef was out and the back up chef well .. they were not on their A or B game ... The dining area was not that busy yet food took 30 mins for soup that was cold and was sent back .. then we waited over an hour for scallops that .. yep cold too.  That's 90 mins for cold soup and cold scallops.   0 for 2.  Although  everyone was apologetic stating  'this is not up to our standards' we are a Charlie Palmer property blah..blah..blah and took the meal off our bill.  The experience left a sour taste as we have been to Napa many times, stayed at numerous properties who would have done so much more to change the experience other than taking that meal off our bill and apologizing it didn't meet their standards.

The last time we were in Napa we stayed at the Meritage Resort, when we arrived our room wasn't ready until 30 mins after they promised.  When we got to our room we had a bottle of wine, cheese plate, chocolate strawberries and they took $50 off our room just for a 30 mins sanfu ... <name>Marty Herrenschmidt<//name>< date>
1529856619630< /date>
<rating>5<//rating>< text>
Came in to check out the Sky & Vine Rooftop Bar... if you want service at a table or one of the fire pits, you'll need to book reservations. Walk-ins are welcome for either of the 2 bar areas and the standing area at the larger one is perfect for enjoying a cocktail and taking in the perfect scenery. This place gets packed at sundown on warm nights, thanks to it's breathtaking view of the sun setting beyond the backdrop of the Napa hills. Drinks and food of course are going to be on the more pricey end for this kind of experience and the staff definitely takes for granted that the tourists coming in will tip large regardless of the service level. That was the only major disappointment. Service was very, very slow despite ample staff on hand. Worth checking out on occasion and perfect for groups wanting a view and comfort but not ideal if you expect the high level of service offered at the many other establishments in Napa.< /text>
<Pictures>None<//Pictures>< resp>
{'time': 1529953132607, 'text': 'Hi, Marty! Thank you so much for your review and positive feedback! We are glad to hear that you enjoyed your time at Archer Hotel Napa and Sky & Vine Rooftop Bar. However, we do regret to hear that the service was less than perfect, and we will be sure to address these issues with the appropriate team members immediately. We hope to welcome you back again for a more positive experience.'}<//resp>

Very disappointing stay.
Our first impression of the lobby and room were outstanding. Unfortunately everything went down hill from there. My wife and I encountered numerous issues which make us discourage anyone from staying here. <Review>We just celebrated my wife's bday at The Archer Rooftop and I have to say we got some of the best customer service. Special thanks to our Bartender for our event Christopher, he was always ready to take another order and fast at making some of the best cocktails I've had. He anticipated people's needs and remembered many people's specific drinks without being told twice.

I would also like to thank David our chef for the evening who whipped us up some of most tasty pasta dishes. David was very friendly and made sure to engage with our guests as well as went above and beyond by getting shredded fresh cheese from downtowns as a last minute request. I would recommend David to anyone looking for a chef.

Lauren with banquets as well as Katana were wonderful and need to also be recognized for exceptional service. Katana was always so kind and helpful with all our requests. Katana anticipated our needs before we even could ask, that's the kind of service you expect in Napa. Both were great to meet and glad we had them on our special event.

I'd recommend the customer service and hospitslity of The Archer Hotel to anyone.

Now, the room we stayed in 443 was adequate. The only two problems we had were the bathroom rolling door fall off the track twice which is a hazard cause could hurt someone. I lifted it to place it back on track. The second was we forgot to put the DND light one and housekeeping tried to walk in early.
